$ Windows PE

PE stands for *Preinstallation Environment*.

Windows PE is bootable from media such as CD-Rom, → hardware/USB[USB flash drive], hard disks etc. The base version (without added drivers, packages or apps) requires only 512 MB of memory.

Windows PE is used to 
  • Automate the installation of a → Windows system on a systm where no previous Windows installation is found 
  • Deploying Windows
  • Repair → Windows/versions/10 desktop editions 

WinPE is an add-on to the ADK (Windows Assesment and Deployment Kit).
